<subSubSection id="B4532CBA8C54B6D6A6D6341D8F93432F" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="02098500A4B2F59A884B80A130D8EC13" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="980985AE717374D70A8A7F296D0771C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
The body proportions of this species are different than in other 
<taxonomicName id="7CAF70AD579CE90957B3F85026571197" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pachyballus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pachyballus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DF31ED2860AEFA2EDC84332030CB3E64" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Pachyballus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., namely width of carapace and width of abdomen are clearly greater than their length. Sigilla are strongly marked. Shape of the eye field is more trapezoid than in congeners, its width at posterior eye row is a quarter larger than anterior width.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
